cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use CompanionBench in research or software, please cite it as below. This is a public-alpha release (0.1.0-alpha) — cite the specific commit/tag you used, since tasks, scoring, and results are expected to change before a stable v0.1."
type: software
title: "CompanionBench: an open-source benchmark for human-like companion communication in LLMs"
version: 0.1.0-alpha
date-released: 2026-07-02
url: "https://github.com/ErbolTakhirov/Benchmark"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ErbolTakhirov/Benchmark"
license: Apache-2.0
authors:
  - name: "CompanionBench contributors"
abstract: >-
  CompanionBench is an API-first, open-source benchmark for evaluating LLM companions and
  proactive assistants across realistic, multi-turn conversations. It jointly measures initiative
  relevance, intervention timing, emotional attunement, preference adaptation, abstention, and
  safety boundaries, using rule-based, deterministic, reproducible scoring. It is model- and
  vendor-neutral: any provider or model set can be evaluated through a small async adapter
  contract.
keywords:
  - llm
  - benchmark
  - evaluation
  - companion
  - proactive-assistant
  - emotional-intelligence
  - agents
